  <td>
   
   <font class="ArticleSource"><big>Spell Changes:</big></font>
   <font class="ArticleHead"><big>4/9/02 Patch</big></font>
   <font class="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </font><font class="ArticleAuthor">Remelio Gemweaver</font>
   <div align="right">
   <font class="ArticleTime">04/10/2002 12:41 AM CDT &nbsp;&nbsp; 4 Comments</font>
   <div align="left">
   <font class="ArticleText">Here are this week's changes... enjoy!  <p> <br><B>New Spells</B><p>- Acumen (SHM 56) - Self Only version of Acumen - This probably is just testing as it has the same name<p> <br><B>Modified Spells</B><p>- ALL PET SPELLS - Recast and Recovery (time it takes for all gems to un-grey) reversed, Cast times unchanged, Component costs down to 1 - This means you can summon them quicker after memming the spell, but your gems stay greyed out longer after you actually cast the pet.  For instance, it now takes my gems 24 seconds to un-grey after casting my level 55 enc, also it only cost me 1 tiny dagger to cast instead of 3.<p>- Cure Blindness (CLR 5, SHM 9) - Effect was changed - Hopefully its fixed now<p>- Cancel Magic (BST 39) - Now usable by beastlords<p>- Mend Bones (NEC 8) - Removes disease counters - Probably so you can un-slow your pet, still has the heal on it<p>- Renew Elements (MAG 8) - Removes disease counters - Probably so you can un-slow your pet, still has the heal on it<p>- Sharik's Replenishing (BST 9) - Removes disease counters - I think you get the picture ;)<p>- Keshuval's Rejuvination (BST 15) - Removes disease counters<p>- Renew Summoning (MAG 20) - Removes disease counters<p>- Shadow Sight (NEC 24, SHD 49) - Now grants See Invisible as well as Ultravision<p>- Renew Bones (NEC 29) - Removes disease counters<p>- Herikol's Soothing (BST 30) - Removes disease counters<p>- Chilling Embrace (NEC 39) - Now adds poison counters - Can't be dispelled, has to be cured now<p>- Yekan's Recovery (BST 39) - Removes disease counters<p>- Vigor of Zehkes (BST 49) - Removes disease counters<p>- Transon's Elemental Infusion (MAG 52) - Removes disease counters<p>- Aid of Khurenz (BST 52) - Removes disease counters<p>- Rage of Zomm (MAG 55) - Recast delay set to 2.25, no recovery time (was recast of 120 seconds)<p>- Sha's Restoration (BST 55) - Removes disease counters<p>- Flaming Sword of Xuzl (WIZ 59) - Recast delay set to 2.25, no recovery time (was recast of 60 seconds)<p>- Transon's Elemental Renewal (MAG 60) - Removes disease counters<p> <br><B>New Effects</B><p>- Vengence - Adds ATK - 5, 10, 15, 20, 30, 50 ATK versions all w/ same name<p>- Icicle Aura - -3 Damage Shield - Cursed item possibly? Mob gets healed for 3 damage every time it hits you<p>- Blessing of the Harvest - AOE Bread - Probably summons 1 for everybody in range<p>- Blessing of the Storm - AOE Water - Probably summons 1 for everybody in range<p>- Brilliance of Ro - Decrease fizzle % - Like Intellectual Superiority<p>- Endurance - Decrease sta loss, increase atk by 5, lasts 60 mins - I like the spell text.. &quot;you feel as if you could run forever&quot;<p>- Mana Shield - Magic Damage only Rune for 150pts, lasts a mere 600 minutes<p>- Donlo's Dementia - Shrinks you 34%, location based aoe - Apparently Donlo doesn't like tall people?<p>- Word of Passage - Port to -376 x +868 in Acrylia Caverns<p>- Allure of the Pool - Port to -484 x +940 in Acrylia Caverns<p>- Tortured Memory - 400 point damage point blank aoe<p>- Will of the Master - Dispells you, changes you into something (probably grimling), decrease max hp by 500, decrease atk by 150 lasts 5 mins, checks no resist, looks like can be cast every 12 seconds - particularly nasty as this doesn't really do damage to you, it decreases your MAX hp by 500, as well as dispelling you<p>- Allure of the Pool(2) - Port to -484 x +940 in Acrylia Caverns - Just when you thought it was safe to get back in the water<p>- Tendrils of Apathy - decrease movement by 65%, slows you for 35%, lasts 1.8 minutes, target based aoe<p>- Deathly Facade - Nuke for 200, changes you to a skeleton, feigns you, dots you for 800 hp in 3 ticks, location based aoe<p>- Gruszia's Grasp - Lifetap for 1200, resist vs magic - Probably a mob proc<p>- Random Teleport 37 - Port to -375 x 540 in Acrylia Caverns - I knew they were running out of spell names but geez guys ;)<p>- Call of Alarm - Summons Player a'la CoH<p>- Blessing of Vah Kerrath - 8 point damage shield, ultravision, 20 atk, 8 point regen per tick, 8 point mana regen per tick, lasts 60 minutes - Yum!<p>- River's Rancor - Nuke for 85, pushes target 1 foot - checks vs magic, pushing helps interrupt casting<p>- Fiery Retribution - Nuke for 95, pushes target 1 foot - checks vs fire<p>- Furor of the Wild - Nuke for 100, pushes target 1 foot - checks vs cold, so put that resist gear on so Furor doesn't push you around<p>- Incinerating Spirit - Cancel Magic x2<p>- Torrent of Ice - nuke for 160, aoe around target, looks like a rain w/ 3 waves<p>- Freezing Scourge - 270 DoT in 1.8 mins, slows 30%<p>- Wrath of the Wild - Nuke for 75, pushes target 1 foot<p>- Coils of Temptation - Stun for 10 seconds, Decrease aggro 100%, Cancel Magic, marked Beneficial, lasts 30 seconds - no outdoors restriction, some sort of single target harmony<p>- Bewildering Dementia - Fear, Decrease aggro 100%, marked Beneficial, lasts 30 seconds - Some sort of super fear?  Fire and forget w/ no trains<p>- Frigid Dominion - 6 second stun, Nuke for 60, Cold Resist<p>- Discorded Terror - Fear, Blind, Decrease aggro 100%, marked Beneficial, lasts 5 minutes - Ok this is the super fear<p>- Entrapment of Dreams - Stun, Cancel Magic x2, point blank aoe, lasts 12 seconds<p>- Frozen Torrent - Nuke for 100, aoe around target, looks like rain w/ 3 waves<p>- Annulling Spirit - Cancel Magic x2, 40% slow, point blank aoe, lasts 5 minutes<p>- Dominion of Force - Stun for 10 seconds, point blank aoe, resists vs fire<p>- Hail of Ice - Nuke for 200, aoe around target, looks like rain w/ 3 waves<p>- Jaydrox Rocks - Spin target, self only - this is something you eat, Jaydrox isn't trying to say he &quot;rocks&quot;<p>- Curse of Walking Sleep - 35% slow, check vs magic, 6 min duration<p>- Curse of Turgur - 75% slow, check vs magic, 6 min duration<p>- Also the usual beta spells and glitchy weird spells as usual<p> <br><B>Modified Effects</B><p>- Fury of the Vah Shir - Something was changed with the effect and possibly the duration but I'm not sure what<p>- Carnage - Emerald added as the reagent<p>- Naki's Lesser Pernicity - Now effects spells with casting times &gt;3 <9.5 - previously only effected spells >4 <9.5

- Naki's Charm of Pernicity - Now effects spells with casting times >3 <9.5 - previously only effected spells >4 <9.5

-  Naki's Greater Pernicity - Now effects spells with casting times >3 <9.5 - previously only effected spells >4 <9.5

- Restore Companion - Removes disease counters

- Annul Self - Removes lots of disease counters
</font>
  </td>
 </tr>
